# scripts/fleet/hosts — GNU parallel --sshloginfile format.
# Copy to scripts/fleet/hosts and edit.  (The real `hosts` is gitignored.)
#
# One worker per line:
#   hostname          ssh to hostname (uses ~/.ssh/config; key-based, non-interactive)
#   user@hostname     explicit user
#   :                 this machine (run locally, no ssh)
#   # comment         ignored; blank lines ignored
#
# A leading "N/" sets job slots, but this harness forces -j1 — ONE all-core,
# multithreaded solver per host — so leave it off.  Heterogeneous speed
# self-balances: parallel refills a host's single slot the instant it finishes a
# shard, so a 2x-faster box completes ~2x the shards.  That only works with many
# small shards (shards >> hosts), so keep --per small and --shards large.
#
# The coordinator (whoever runs run.sh) need not appear here — list a box only if
# you want it to do work.  Example: two remote workers + this machine.
worker-7950x3d
slow-laptop
:
